The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the concept of edge-colorability and the minimum number of edges or vertices that need to be removed to obtain a certain level of colorability. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and the paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which could fit under computer science and discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also relates to graph theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and combinatorial optimization (cs.CO) as it involves finding optimal solutions to certain graph problems.
